details: SEIZURE WARNING!!! Hi! It's me/you/us/them again. I have another reminder for you - "You will have everything you need to fulfill your Vision. You have to have the Vision!" Here we go again with another experiment. Has taken me some months to figure out basic 3D from scratch, but finally feeling a little bit more confident about the future pieces, especially in VR :) This time focusing more on the overall feeling, since I was suddenly inspired and missed a lot of details on the way due to fear of scrapping the entire piece due to getting stuck in details :D Huge thanks to every single girl who answered my last-day call for vocals on Instagram, I didnt expect to get any submissions, yet alone voices from all continents. Please remember, that these experiences are very subjective so don't take this as a reference to "how it might be for you", please do your research :) Even when taking subjectivity in the count, remember that I'm just learning to recreate these things and all my pieces are "work-in-progress", so I can gather your input and grow the objective value of my passion work. I already know that audio sucks :D , this was the first time in my life trying to do something more advanced than just basic fading and FX. As always, I'd like to hear your feedback, By the way, if you feel like youtube has destroyed the quality of this and would like to see it in higher quality, feel free to check my Patreon page (https://www.patreon.com/stingrayz), my Patrons get access to uncompressed versions of my work :) Most of my content can be found here: https://www.symmetric-vision.xyz/ https://gfycat.com/@stingrayz https://www.instagram.com/inner.refle... https://www.facebook.com/symmetryinvi... https://www.patreon.com/stingrayz By the way, if you'd like to have a tangible object with my design on it including the entity at the end of the video (on a face mask), feel free to check out https://www.symmetric-vision.xyz/shop/ I also do custom orders, so if you'd like something made specifically for you feel free to contact me :) Thank You for being here with me all this time! Have an amazing day!
text:
SEIZURE WARNING!!!

Hi! 
It's me/you/us/them again. I have another reminder for you - "You will have everything you need to fulfill your Vision. You have to have the Vision!"

Here we go again with another experiment. Has taken me some months to figure out basic 3D from scratch, but finally feeling a little bit more confident about the future pieces, especially in VR :)
This time focusing more on the overall feeling, since I was suddenly inspired and missed a lot of details on the way due to fear of scrapping the entire piece due to getting stuck in details :D 

Huge thanks to every single girl who answered my last-day call for vocals on Instagram, I didnt expect to get any submissions, yet alone voices from all continents.

Please remember, that these experiences are very subjective so don't take this as a reference to "how it might be for you", please do your research :) Even when taking subjectivity in the count, remember that I'm just learning to recreate these things and all my pieces are "work-in-progress", so I can gather your input and grow the objective value of my passion work. 
I already know that audio sucks :D , this was the first time in my life trying to do something more advanced than just basic fading and FX.
As always, I'd like to hear your feedback,

By the way, if you feel like youtube has destroyed the quality of this and would like to see it in higher quality, feel free to check my Patreon page (https://www.patreon.com/stingrayz), my Patrons get access to uncompressed versions of my work :)

Most of my content  can be found here:

I also do custom orders, so if you'd like something made specifically for you feel free to contact me :)

Thank You for being here with me all this time!
Have an amazing day!

details: Dr. Advait Kulkarni | Appointment booking number: 08310021492 Consultant Neurologist | HSR Neuro Clinic, Bangalore Warning Signs of a Seizure, they can feel the seizure coming. Some of them may feel severe headache, giddiness sense of fear, sense of fullness in abdomen, sense of discomfort sense of familiarity in unfamiliar places, called as déjà vu. A few patients my get few jerks, which are coming before seizure, sit is very important to become aware . some patients may stare before a seizure, some my have lip movements like lip automatism or some swallowing movements or some may have hand movements or hand automatism before a seizure. So seizure can be prevented. Some tips are very important to prevent seizure. These are having a proper good night sleep. Sleep deprivation is one of the most common causes of seizure. Avoid overexertion. Any physical exertion overnight trekking or physical activities like sports can trigger seizure. Excess alcohol can trigger seizure. So it is better to avoid smoking and alcohol to prevent seizure. Some of the drugs, antibiotics can cause seizure, patients who are drug addicts get seizure when they suddenly stop taking the drug. A person who is addicted to alcohol if he suddenly stops, then when he is using it daily can also cause seizure. #seizure #EpilepsySigns

details: Watch more Epilepsy & Seizure Disorders videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/502009-... You know whenever anybody comes into the office they always ask us, first thing, about whether epilepsy can be triggered by strobe lights, and people often think back to when the first Pokemon movies came out and all those children in Japan seized during the movie, so photosensitive epilepsy is something that people worry about all the time. On all those video games there are those warnings that say, you know, you shouldn't play this game in case you have epilepsy, but only one specific type of epilepsy has photosensitivity to it and that's a generalized epilepsy. So that's when the whole brain turns on at once. Lights up all at once, there is a big burst of electricity through the whole brain. It's one of the reflex epilepsies. So kids with epilepsy, for the most part, can play video games and can go under strobe lights, unless they very specifically sieze when they are under strobe lights, and when we do the EEGs, when we do the tests of their brain waves we actually flash lights at them to see if it does create a siezure. So by doing the EEG and by flashing the lights in the child's eyes, and having the EEG running at the same time, we can conclusively tell families whether the children can play video games or not play video games and that will make a child very happy, hopefully, to find out that it's perfectly safe to play the video games and that they don't have photosensitive epilepsy. As well as the teenagers and the young adults that will call or text and say, can I go, we're going to a party, and I know there will be strobe lights, is that okay. So at least we have an answer for them after we do the initial EEG.

details: FIRST VIDEO ON THE FIRST DAY OF 2019 WHOO!!! Ahem...heya guys!! Wassup? Happy New Year! 2018 was an...interesting year huh? Welp! It’s time to start fresh y’all! I just want you guys to know if you don’t already, that I appreciate you all sooooo very much!! Your support throughout 2018 really made me happy, and I’m very glad that I decided to make this channel three years ago, I really do value and love you guys don’t EVER forget that okay?!?!?! If you have New Year Resolutions, don’t forget to follow them! I have mine, I hope I’ll follow them though 😂😂 Procrastinating is my weakness... Anywho, I’m back with another meme! I haven’t made one in almost a month so why not? They’re so fun to make! This meme is the Life Letters Meme (but just a tiny bit extended)! When I discovered this meme I immediately wanted to make my own version, but of course, my channel is not all about stopmotion memes, so I need to get into the habit of making different types of videos yanno know what I mean? Nonetheless this was SUPER fun to make! It only took me a couple of days due to all the editing I had to put into it, but it was obviously worth it! If you guys didn’t notice by now, this video has a lil’ story behind it! Here it is: Frankie is not aware of what’s happening to her. She’s starting to realize that she’s losing her mind, and she’s losing it quick. So she decides to do something she doesn’t want to do, she isolates herself without anyone knowing. She doesn’t want to be found by her friends, family and loved ones because she doesn’t want to hurt them with her condition. Though she misses them dearly, especially her significant other Neighthan Rot, she wants to do what’s right and seclude herself until her illness shuts all of her organs down and kills her. Her mental state is beyond corrupted, Frankie experiences myriads of hallucinations and develops dark thoughts that she can’t get rid of. But no one can save her. Unfortunately, in the end, Frankie Stein loses her mind completely... Yeah...pretty sad and edgy right? Pfffft, don’t worry, it’s only for the meme! Y’all think it’s a good story or nah? Lmaooo. Anyway, I really hope you all enjoy this, and thanks so much for watching! Like always I put a lot of effort into this so I’m glad I can show you guys the outcome! text:
FIRST VIDEO ON THE FIRST DAY OF 2019 WHOO!!! 

Ahem...heya guys!! Wassup? Happy New Year! 2018 was an...interesting year huh? Welp! It’s time to start fresh y’all! 

I just want you guys to know if you don’t already, that I appreciate you all sooooo very much!! Your support throughout 2018 really made me happy, and I’m very glad that I decided to make this channel three years ago, I really do value and love you guys don’t EVER forget that okay?!?!?! If you have New Year Resolutions, don’t forget to follow them! I have mine, I hope I’ll follow them though 😂😂 Procrastinating is my weakness...

Anywho, I’m back with another meme! I haven’t made one in almost a month so why not? They’re so fun to make! This meme is the Life Letters Meme (but just a tiny bit extended)! When I discovered this meme I immediately wanted to make my own version, but of course, my channel is not all about stopmotion memes, so I need to get into the habit of making different types of videos yanno know what I mean? Nonetheless this was SUPER fun to make! It only took me a couple of days due to all the editing I had to put into it, but it was obviously worth it! If you guys didn’t notice by now, this video has a lil’ story behind it! 

Here it is: Frankie is not aware of what’s happening to her. She’s starting to realize that she’s losing her mind, and she’s losing it quick. So she decides to do something she doesn’t want to do, she isolates herself without anyone knowing. She doesn’t want to be found by her friends, family and loved ones because she doesn’t want to hurt them with her condition. Though she misses them dearly, especially her significant other Neighthan Rot, she wants to do what’s right and seclude herself until her illness shuts all of her organs down and kills her. Her mental state is beyond corrupted, Frankie experiences myriads of hallucinations and develops dark thoughts that she can’t get rid of. But no one can save her. Unfortunately, in the end, Frankie Stein loses her mind completely...

Yeah...pretty sad and edgy right? Pfffft, don’t worry, it’s only for the meme! Y’all think it’s a good story or nah? Lmaooo. Anyway, I really hope you all enjoy this, and thanks so much for watching! Like always I put a lot of effort into this so I’m glad I can show you guys the outcome! All audio in this video does NOT belong to me!

details: #woodspirit #pineknot #dremel [WARNING-VIDEO MAY CAUSE SEIZURES] Thanks for stopping by! This is a promo clip of a piece I just completed. I started it with a bearded man in mind but changed it around removing the beard later on to focus on wrinkles around the mouth. Sometimes the end result is something unplanned for but it takes the turn for the better. Recently I’ve started uploading to this channel to share methods/techniques I’ve learned & developed over the years so that you can take your carvings to the next level and beyond. I post vids on a regular weekly basis which hopefully isn’t hindered with the seasonal farm work I do in the Fall season(I think it’ll be ok). My webpage is: http://wood-psyche.com (It’s terribly in need of updates so bear in mind it’s limited capacity. There’s some fotos of previous work that’s been sold or donated to view. Thank you. Tools used: ~Dremel 370 ~Dremel 332-5 moto-flex ~Saburr coarse spherical bit 1/8” ~Dremel high speed cutter #190/#192 ~Diamond burr spherical 3/32” ~Metal scribe w/ pin vise ~Sandpaper ~Wire wool Also special thanks to frankum-electro- pop & rokzroom-0sc-synth-efx @www.freesound.org for the music.

#woodspirit #pineknot #dremel 

[WARNING-VIDEO MAY CAUSE SEIZURES]

Thanks for stopping by! 

This is a promo clip of a piece I just completed.
I started it with a bearded man in mind but changed
it around removing the beard later on to focus on wrinkles around the mouth. Sometimes the end result is something unplanned for but it takes the turn for the better. 

Recently I’ve started uploading to this channel to share methods/techniques I’ve learned & developed over the years so that you can take your carvings to the next level and beyond.

I post vids on a regular weekly basis which hopefully isn’t hindered with the seasonal farm work I do in the Fall season(I think it’ll be ok).

(It’s terribly in need of updates so bear in mind it’s limited capacity. There’s some fotos of previous work that’s been sold or donated to view.

Thank you.

Tools used:
~Dremel 370
~Dremel 332-5  moto-flex 
~Saburr coarse spherical bit 1/8”
~Dremel high speed cutter #190/#192
~Diamond burr spherical 3/32”
~Metal scribe w/ pin vise
~Sandpaper 
~Wire wool

details: Epilepsy.com Editor-in-Chief Dr. Joseph Sirven worked with students at the Cronkite School of Journalism at Arizona State University to examine general media coverage of various public health issues. The students sought to answer one important question: What kind of news coverage had epilepsy gotten in recent broadcast media? To find out, they used Google search to compile this video montage of broadcast media coverage about epilepsy over the last year. (The students received permission from each station before adding their clip to this video montage.) Let’s do better in November for National Epilepsy Awareness Month – and throughout the year! Learn how to get involved in raising epilepsy awareness at http://www.epilepsy.com/article/2016/...

Oftentimes it’s only a fantasy, but sometimes the surrounding magic is real. Two Worlds synopsis:
Sometimes it feels like a greater force is guiding you through life. Oftentimes it’s only a fantasy, but sometimes the surrounding magic is real. Two Worlds is a musical journey to the human condition, depicted from the perspective of three individuals who are trying to overcome obstacles in their minds. First, they will have to come to peace with who they are in order to let go of the ego. But what is behind the momentum of life? Is existence random in its nature or are events predetermined?

Rising duo Animistic Beliefs tease their album Mindset:Reset with an electrifying visual for their track ‘An Eye For A.I.’ The Rotterdam duo has utilized their bespoke setup and expansive list of influences to create a contemporary electro record, opening a window into a world of both mythical and futuristic views.
